 :quote chapter and verse: v. [by analogy with the mainstream phrase] To cite
a relevant excerpt from an appropriate {bible}. "I don't care if rn gets it
wrong; `Followup-To: poster' is explicitly permitted by {RFC}-1036. I'll
quote chapter and verse if you don't believe me." see also {legalese},
{language lawyer}, {RTFS} (sense 2).